Focus files: app/wwdos_app.cpp, app/command_registry.cpp

TASK: Fix window placement so windows can NEVER be positioned off-screen. This must be enforced at the C++ level so no agent or API call can create invisible windows.

## What to fix

### 1. app/wwdos_app.cpp — api_resize_window and api_move_window

Both functions use `w->locate(newBounds)` to position windows. Add clamping BEFORE the locate() call:

- Get desktop extent: `TRect desk = TProgram::deskTop->getExtent();`
- Clamp the window bounds so it stays fully within the desktop:
  - If newBounds.b.x > desk.b.x, shift left (and shrink if wider than desktop)
  - If newBounds.b.y > desk.b.y, shift up (and shrink if taller than desktop)
  - If newBounds.a.x < desk.a.x, shift right
  - If newBounds.a.y < desk.a.y, shift down
  - Minimum size: 10 wide, 5 tall
- After clamping, call locate() with the clamped bounds

### 2. app/command_registry.cpp — snap_window handler

The snap_window handler already computes x, y, w, h from fractional zones. After the computation (around line 845-850), add the same clamping logic before calling api_resize_window and api_move_window.

### 3. app/wwdos_app.cpp — the create_window / spawn path

Find where new windows are spawned via API (search for "create_window" or "open_window" or "spawn"). Ensure new windows are clamped to desktop bounds after initial placement.

## Approach

Write a helper function that takes a TRect and the desktop TRect and returns a clamped TRect. Call it from all three locations. Something like:

```cpp
static TRect clampToDesktop(TRect bounds, TRect desk) {
    int minW = 10, minH = 5;
    int w = bounds.b.x - bounds.a.x;
    int h = bounds.b.y - bounds.a.y;
    // Ensure minimum size
    if (w < minW) w = minW;
    if (h < minH) h = minH;
    // Clamp to desktop size
    if (w > desk.b.x - desk.a.x) w = desk.b.x - desk.a.x;
    if (h > desk.b.y - desk.a.y) h = desk.b.y - desk.a.y;
    // Position within desktop
    int x = bounds.a.x;
    int y = bounds.a.y;
    if (x + w > desk.b.x) x = desk.b.x - w;
    if (y + h > desk.b.y) y = desk.b.y - h;
    if (x < desk.a.x) x = desk.a.x;
    if (y < desk.a.y) y = desk.a.y;
    return TRect(x, y, x + w, y + h);
}
```

Put this as a static function in wwdos_app.cpp (near the top, before api_move_window).

Build after: cd build && make -j$(sysctl -n hw.ncpu) wwdos

